Task
Difference between maximum and minimum value in an array
Write a function differenceMaxMin that takes an array arr as an argument and returns the difference between the maximum and minimum value. If the array is empty, return null.
Example:
• the differenceMaxMin ([3, 4, 8, 1]) function must return 7;
• the differenceMaxMin ([7, 7]) function must return 0;
• the differenceMaxMin ([2]) function must return 0;
• the differenceMaxMin ([]) function must return null;

Solution
function differenceMaxMin (arr) {
let max = Math.max (... arr);
   let min = Math.min (... arr);
   if (arr.length === 0) return null;
   else
   return max - min;
}
